The Director General, Press Affairs of the Directorate of Public Enlightenment, Media and Communication in the office of the Governor of Zamfara state, Alhaji Bello Samaila is dead. Aged 67, Bello Samaila, otherwise known as Bello MC, died as a result of a protracted illness and has been buried. The late DG served with The Path newspaper, Sokoto, and was MD/Editor-in-chief with the Zamfara state newspaper Company,  the Legacy newspaper,  before his appointment as the Director-General Press Affairs, according to a statement signed by the Special Adviser, Public Enlightenment, Media and Communication in the office of the Executive Governor, Alhaji Ibrahim Dosara.